<li id="cite_note-birthday-0">^ <a href="#cite_ref-birthday_0-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-birthday_0-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-birthday_0-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFAsimov">Asimov, Isaac. <i>In Memory Yet Green</i>.  "The date of my birth, as I celebrate it, was January 2, 1920. It could not have been later than that. It might, however, have been earlier. Allowing for the uncertainties of the times, of the lack of <a href="/wiki/Civil_registry" title="Civil registry">records</a>, of the <a href="/wiki/Hebrew_calendar" title="Hebrew calendar">Jewish</a> and <a href="/wiki/Julian_calendar" title="Julian calendar">Julian calendars</a>, it might have been as early as October 4, 1919. There is, however, no way of finding out. My parents were always uncertain and it really doesn't matter. I celebrate January 2, 1920, so let it be."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=In+Memory+Yet+Green&amp;rft.aulast=Asimov&amp;rft.aufirst=Isaac&amp;rft.au=Asimov%2C+Isaac&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Isaac_Asimov"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
